qDef.qDef:
=Dual(
  'data:image/svg+xml,<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" height="12" width="' & Num(80+$(vPageKnowledgebaseSVGPadPx)) & '">'
  &'<text text-anchor="end" font-family="Source Sans Pro" font-size="9" fill="black">'
  &'<tspan dominant-baseline="central" text-anchor="end" x="' & Num($(vPageKnowledgebaseSVGPadPx)) & '" y="5.5">' 
  & Num([Knowledgebase Pages],'#,##0') & '</tspan></text>'
  & '<rect x="' & Num(5+$(vPageKnowledgebaseSVGPadPx)) & '" y="0" width="50" height="12" style="fill:%23F0F3F6" />'
  & '<rect x="' & Num(5+$(vPageKnowledgebaseSVGPadPx)) & '" y="2" width="' & RangeMin(Round([% Knowledgebase Pages to Quota]*100/2,1),50) & '" height="8" style="fill:%23' & If(Num([% Knowledgebase Pages to Quota])<$(vPagesLowThresh),'$(vBelowLowThreshColor)',If(Num([% Knowledgebase Pages to Quota])<$(vPagesHighThresh),'$(vBelowHighThreshColor)','$(vAboveHighThreshColor)')) & '" />' 
  &'<text text-anchor="start" font-family="Source Sans Pro" font-size="9" fill="black">'
  &'<tspan dominant-baseline="central" text-anchor="middle" x="' & Num(68+$(vPageKnowledgebaseSVGPadPx)) & '" y="5.5">' 
  & Num([% Knowledgebase Pages to Quota],'#,##0%') & '</tspan></text>'
  & '</svg>',
  Num([% Knowledgebase Pages to Quota])
)
If([Distinct Documents Referenced in Answers] / [Knowledgebase Documents]>1,Dual('>100%',1.1),Num([Distinct Documents Referenced in Answers] / [Knowledgebase Documents],'##0%'))

qAttributeExpressions.qExpression: {1}If((1-[% Documents Referenced in Answers])>=.75 AND [% Documents Referenced in Answers]<>0,$(c_red_alpha(((1 - [% Documents Referenced in Answers]) * 25500) / 100)))
If([Knowledgebase Days Since Last Index]>=$(vu_knowledgebase_stale_days),$(c_red_alpha([Knowledgebase Days Since Last Index])))

qMsg.qv: ='There are no knowledgebases found within the current selection state.'

)

This is a set of supported objects that will facilitate dashboard creation in Qlik Sense. These can be used in addition to the objects found under "Charts".

For limitations and support conditions, see the documentation.

extensionMeta.name: Layout container
extensionMeta.description: The layout container object has a canvas that can hold multiple objects. In this container you can freely move objects around, as well as position the objects on top of each other or overlapping.
extensionMeta.author: QlikTech International AB
